@NODE What "What ist superup & superup_gui"

o What ist superup
  ----------------

superup enables you to upload files from a script 
or from the DOS-Shell to any filearea.
  
superup is FREE-WARE, but if you like it feel free to send
me a postcard from your city. It's nice to know that someone
uses my utility.

superup will be optimized, this was a fast programmed version
cause all the available uploaders dont work more since some
changes in the dlg file strucure.

o What ist superup_gui
  --------------------

superup_gui is only a GUI interface for superup

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"

o Usage
  =====

  superup
  -------

      copy superup into a directory added in your path command.

      superup uses the commands c:copy and c:filenote for copying
      and for set the filenotes.

      superup also uses the dlg.library, i'm sure you have
      already install it, don't you ?  :-)

      Let's start now : type superup for help

      Usage: superup -f <filename> -a <areanumber> -d <description> -u <uploader> -r <ratio y or n>

      -f <filename>      is the path of the file which is to be uploaded.

      -a <areanumber>    is the place where the file should be uploaded to.

      -d <description>   is a short description that will be placed in the
                         header-file           

      -u <uploader>      the name that will be shown as Uploader in the
                         header-file.

      -r <ratio y or n>  y=use ratio n=file is FREE



  superup_gui
  -----------

      superup_gui needs the reqtools.library in LIBS: and superup somewhere
      in your path.

       
      
                         
    
@ENDNODE

